,Not Recommended,311910,12655254,"Posted: 27 October, 2014",all,Evilworm,"I write this on the 27th October, almost two weeks after release. No patches yet. I might change my view later if the developer decides to upgrade Dig It! to something better, but I doubt it.This game has the potential to be a nice game. But it isn't a good game as it is when I write this. The areas you can ""work"" in, are so small you would belive it is an actual sandbox. You can hardly turn your vehicle inside some of the places (reminds me of Austin Powers - The Spy Who Shagged Me, where he has to turn between two walls). The developer team chose to have awkward key combinations, instead of making them intuitive. You never have to drive the trucks and deliver sand or gravel, just drive to the gate and it is empty. How can they call that a simulator? Its not even close!Bugs. Lots of bugs and problems:-People are reporting they can't dig (it is a DIGGING SIMULATOR!!).-If you can dig, you can scrape the ground and get a pile of dirt from nothing. In fact you can produce dirt from nothing.-Camera is crap! I wonder how the developers played this game without noticing the camera-bugs.-If you try to exit a vehicle close to another object, you start to fly... you can see the whole city from up in the air while you fall down again.-There is no animation for the people sitting in the machines. None at all! How come the developers never did think of that?Conclusion: I would give this game a 1.5/10 (where 0.5 points is for nice colours). I recommend you give your money to charity instead of buying this game."
